"{\"uid\": \"greekreporter.com-2025-03-06-divine-dinners-greek-christian-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The recent Olympics controversy surrounding the Feast of the Gods and the Last Supper has renewed interest in divine dinners.These celestial suppers symbolize divine intervention, covenant-making, and the intertwining of gods with the mortals.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite their vast differences in context and purpose, the events are also remarkably similar.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They reflect how a simple meal can foreshadow monumental events, illuminating gripping insights into the ancient Greek and Christian worlds.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.874482909001164e-18, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\"}, {\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The divine dinner on Mount Olympus is a scene to behold.\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 503, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.861201100160203e-53, \"text\": \"Mount Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The marriage of Thetis, a sea nymph, and Peleus, a mortal king, is a celestial affair bridging the divine and mortal realms.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 555, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.359788469009694e-73, \"text\": \"Thetis\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\"}, {\"begin\": 580, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peleus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4856706707719106e-68, \"text\": \"Peleus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peleus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peleus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Attended by the cr\\u00e8me de la cr\\u00e8me of the Greek pantheon-Zeus, Hera, and Poseidon, among others-this event is not merely a social gathering but a significant turning point inGreek mythology.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 705, \"end\": 710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.386099750496636e-16, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.578762661632539e-50, \"text\": \"Hera\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\"}, {\"begin\": 736, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poseidon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.236201956938281e-58, \"text\": \"Poseidon\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poseidon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poseidon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It leads to the birth ofAchillesand ultimately influences theTrojan War.The gods, with their power and presence, make this event one of monumental importance.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, the Last Supper\\u00a0is an intimate, somber gathering of Jesus and his twelve apostles.\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This meal marks Jesus' final meal before his crucifixion and is central to Christian theology.\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It symbolizes the establishment of a New Covenant between God and humanity.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper sets the stage for the Passion of Christ, leading to his sacrifice and subsequent resurrection, foundational to Christian beliefs.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1409, \"end\": 1418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This meal, heavy with meaning, highlights themes of sacrifice, redemption, and divine love.\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Both events gather key figures in their respective traditions.\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The divine banquet includesZeus, Hera, andPoseidonin addition to other deities.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1617, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.578762661632539e-50, \"text\": \"Hera\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These each represent various aspects of the cosmos and human experience.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their presence underscores the event's significance and the interconnectedness of divine affairs with mortal destinies.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each god and goddess, with their distinct domain and power, adds to the grandeur and importance of the occasion.\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the Last Supper involves Jesus and his apostles, pivotal figures in the Christian narrative.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2007, \"end\": 2012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jesus, the Son of God, shares this critical moment with his closest followers, who will become the leaders of the early Christian Church.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The apostles' presence highlights the transition from Jesus' earthly ministry to the spread of his teachings following his resurrection.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2267, \"end\": 2272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a moment of profound significance, marking the beginning of a new chapter in Christian history.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2433, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Symbolism abounds in both events.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The gods' behavior and interactions at the divine banquet often reflect their domains and powers.\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apollo might be depicted playing the lyre, symbolizing music and prophecy, while Dionysus may be shown with wine, representing festivity and ecstasy.\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2585, \"end\": 2591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3073683584406697e-30, \"text\": \"Apollo\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apollo\"}, {\"begin\": 2666, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.449556238903387e-38, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These symbolic acts reinforce the gods' identities and roles within the mythological framework, adding layers of meaning to the event.\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Last Supper, Jesus' actions are profoundly symbolic.\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He breaks bread and shares wine with his disciples, declaring them hisbody and blood.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This act institutes the Eucharist, a central sacrament in Christianity.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3041, \"end\": 3050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrifice\", \"score\": 0.9577494139146933, \"rank\": 0.044114447340347286, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrifice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sacrifice\"}, {\"begin\": 3075, \"end\": 3087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999881994036117, \"rank\": 1.1800735781612272e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The symbolism of the bread and wine as Jesus' body and blood signifies the new covenant and Jesus' impending sacrifice for humanity's redemption.\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3128, \"end\": 3133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These acts are laden with theological significance and have inspired centuries of Christian practice and reflection.\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3317, \"end\": 3326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both dinners foreshadow significant events.\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The divine dinner indirectly leads to the Trojan War.\", \"from\": 3397, \"to\": 3450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eris, the goddess of discord, was not invited to the banquet and, in her anger, threw a golden apple inscribed \\\"To the fairest,\\\" which led to the judgment of Paris and the eventual war.\", \"from\": 3451, \"to\": 3636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3451, \"end\": 3455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.46360442006142e-36, \"text\": \"Eris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\"}, {\"begin\": 3609, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999976930667, \"rank\": 2.3070169202198775e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her vengeful ploy illustrates how a slighted deity's actions can unleash chaos and conflict, underscoring the interconnectedness and often unintended consequences of divine and mortal actions.\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, the Last Supper directly precedes Jesus' arrest, trial, torture, crucifixion, and resurrection.\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3876, \"end\": 3889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jesus' arrest\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arrest_of_Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Judas Iscariot, one of the apostles, betrays Jesus for thirty pieces of silver, driven by greed and the love of money.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3938, \"end\": 3952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.748076601062719e-75, \"text\": \"Judas Iscariot\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\"}, {\"begin\": 3975, \"end\": 3988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiss_of_Judas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"betrays Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiss_of_Judas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kiss_of_Judas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His actions set into motion a chain of events that lead to Jesus' crucifixion.\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4116, \"end\": 4121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Eris, Judas is a disgruntled figure whose actions precipitate disaster, though, in his case, the motivation is not revenge but financial gain.\", \"from\": 4136, \"to\": 4283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4141, \"end\": 4145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.46360442006142e-36, \"text\": \"Eris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Children_of_Ares\"}, {\"begin\": 4147, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2952984440680756e-33, \"text\": \"Judas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judas_Iscariot\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This betrayal underscores human frailty and the devastating impact a single individual's choices can have on a larger narrative.\", \"from\": 4284, \"to\": 4412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The context and nature of these dinners differ significantly.\", \"from\": 4414, \"to\": 4475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The divine banquet is a mythological event set in the grandeur ofMount Olympus, celebrating a marriage and the union of divine and mortal realms.\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4547, \"end\": 4554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.5351955174578e-30, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It reflects the ancient Greeks' view of their gods as powerful yet capricious beings directly influencing human affairs.\", \"from\": 4622, \"to\": 4742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4638, \"end\": 4652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.999999998756266, \"rank\": 1.243897051228482e-09, \"text\": \"ancient Greeks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper, however, involves historical figures, notably Jesus of Nazareth.\", \"from\": 4744, \"to\": 4825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4807, \"end\": 4812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 4816, \"end\": 4824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazareth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.775117394642594e-35, \"text\": \"Nazareth\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazareth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazareth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event is the cornerstone of Christian theology, representing key themes of sacrifice, atonement, and the new covenant between God and humanity.\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has inspired countless theological reflections, liturgical practices, and artistic representations, underscoring its centrality to Christian faith and worship.\", \"from\": 4974, \"to\": 5136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5108, \"end\": 5117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cultural and religious contexts of these events are distinct.\", \"from\": 5138, \"to\": 5203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The divine dinner is part of Greek mythology, a rich tapestry of stories explaining natural phenomena, human behavior, and cultural practices.\", \"from\": 5204, \"to\": 5346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5233, \"end\": 5248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4549491765129796e-22, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These myths were integral to the ancient Greeks' understanding of the world and their place within it.\", \"from\": 5347, \"to\": 5449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5380, \"end\": 5394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.999999998756266, \"rank\": 1.243897051228482e-09, \"text\": \"ancient Greeks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper, however, is a linchpin of Christian theology.\", \"from\": 5451, \"to\": 5513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It embodies themes of sacrifice, atonement, and divine-human relationship.\", \"from\": 5514, \"to\": 5588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has fueled countless theological debates, liturgical traditions, and artistic endeavors, reflecting its deep significance in Christian belief.\", \"from\": 5589, \"to\": 5734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5717, \"end\": 5726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though separated by time, culture, and context, there are intriguing parallels between the divine dinner celebrating Thetis and Peleus and Jesus' Last Supper.\", \"from\": 5736, \"to\": 5894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5853, \"end\": 5859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.359788469009694e-73, \"text\": \"Thetis\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thetis\"}, {\"begin\": 5875, \"end\": 5880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9993980385871923, \"rank\": 0.0006023239887629835, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Significant figures are gathered for a meal, there are symbolic acts involved, and major events are foreshadowed.\", \"from\": 5895, \"to\": 6008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These divine dinners in ancient Greek and Christian traditions reflect the diverse ways in which the act of sitting down for food becomes more than merely a meal.\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6033, \"end\": 6046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.874482909001164e-18, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_religion\"}, {\"begin\": 6051, \"end\": 6060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999993888196, \"rank\": 6.113385371514655e-10, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a sacred act during which heaven and earth collide, and history can be written with every passing plate.\", \"from\": 6172, \"to\": 6282, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See all thelatest newsfrom Greece and the world atGreekreporter.com.Contact our newsroomto report an update or send your story, photos and videos.\", \"from\": 6284, \"to\": 6430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6311, \"end\": 6317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.655122503929919e-16, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow GR onGoogle Newsandsubscribe hereto our daily email!\", \"from\": 6431, \"to\": 6490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Copyright - GreekReporter.com\", \"from\": 6492, \"to\": 6523, \"entities\": []}]}"